DeepRacer Model Training Summary (Teacher Share Version)
Date: April 5, 2026

Objective
- Build a stable local DeepRacer training workflow on Mac and reach safe, consistent lane-following quality before any physical-car testing.

What was achieved
- Local runtime setup and custom-file upload flow are working.
- Headless simulation path was stabilized (display/render crashes were resolved).
- Short and medium training runs were completed and measured multiple times.
- Evidence reports and metrics were captured for review.

Attempt outcomes (high level)
1) 30-minute baseline run
- Runtime: completed
- Quality: low consistency
- Key numbers: eval avg completion ~11.55, best eval completion 31, off-track 100%
- Result: NO-GO

2) 60-minute run
- Runtime: OOM termination
- Key numbers: eval avg completion ~12.37, best eval completion 23, off-track 100%
- Result: NO-GO

3) Recovery-tuned run
- Runtime: progressed, then OOM
- Key numbers: train_last20 11.35, eval_last20 22.13, best_eval_completion 23, off-track 100%
- Result: NO-GO (better eval average, but still unreliable and below best-completion target)

4) Headless-fix run
- Runtime: stable infrastructure, no render crash signatures
- Key numbers: train_last20 8.15, eval_last20 3.80, best_eval_completion 5, off-track 100%
- Result: FAIL_METRICS

5) Conservative action/reward retry
- Runtime: started stable, then OOM later in run
- Key numbers: training episodes 40, evaluation episodes 8, train_last20 9.45, eval_last20 7.00, best_eval_completion 7, off-track 100%
- Result: NO-GO

Current conclusion
- Infrastructure stability is improved compared to earlier runs, but model quality is still not sufficient.
- Across attempts, off-track remained 100% and evaluation completion stayed too low for safe physical testing.
- Final status for this cycle: NO-GO for physical package.

